   Description

   Tilings and Tessellations is a mathematic school supported by the
   CIMPA. It is primarily dedicated to young researchers and graduate
   students (motivated undergraduated students are also welcome) in
   mathematics from Iran and neighbor countries (grants for travel and
   accomodation are provided). About 60 hours of lectures on tilings shall
   be given by international researchers. Tilings offer a connection
   between combinatorics, computability, discrete geometry, dynamical
   systems and probability theory. Tilings are also related to the
   tessellations that embellish islamic architecture, and wider audience
   lectures shall be given on this subject.

